			<transcript translate="true">Another tool used in successful parenting is attunement. Attunement is defined as the ability to respond with sensitivity to a child's communications and needs. While attachment between parent and child typically occurs in the first year, attunement continues on throughout childhood. Let's look at a situation in which a father is attuned to his child's needs.  Click Play to begin.</transcript>
